# Basic CMD Commands

## Navigation Commands

| Shell Command | Windows Command    | Description             |
| ------------- | ------------------ | ----------------------- |
| `pwd`         | `cd`               | Show current directory  |
| `ls`          | `dir`              | List directory contents |
| `clear`       | `cls`              | Clear screen            |
| `cd ~`        | `cd %UserPorfile%` | Go to home directory    |
| `cd -`        | `cd -`             | Go back to previous dir |
| `cd /`        | `cd \`             | Go to root directory    |
| `cd <path>`   | `cd <path>`        | Go to specific directory|

## File Operations

| Shell Command | Windows Command | Description       |
| ------------- | --------------- | ----------------- |
| `cp`          | `copy`          | Copy files        |
| `mv`          | `move`          | Move/rename files |
| `rm`          | `del`           | Delete files      |
| `mkdir`       | `md`            | Create directory  |
| `touch`       | `type nul >`    | Create empty file |
| `cat`         | `type`          | Display file      |
| `echo`        | `echo`          | Print text        |
| `find`        | `findstr`       | Search text       |


## Examples

### What these commands do

- `cd || pwd`: Shows you where you are in the file system (like the address bar in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `dir || ls`: Lists the files and folders in your current directory (like the contents of a folder in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `cls || clear`: Clears the screen (like pressing F5 in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `cd ~ || cd %UserPorfile%`: Takes you to your home directory (like going to your user folder in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `md || mkdir MyFolder`: Creates a new folder (like creating a new folder in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `type nul > || touch myFile.txt`: Creates a new empty file (like create a new file in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `copy MyFile.txt || cp MyCopy.txt`: Makes a duplicate of your file (just like copy & paste)

- `move || mv OldName.txt NewName.txt`: Renames or moves a file (like renaming a file in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `move "C:\NewFolder" || mv MyFile.txt "/home/NewFolder"`: Moves a file to a different folder (like dragging and dropping a file in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `del || rm Unwanted.txt`: Deletes a file (like deleting a file in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `type MyFile.txt || cat MyFile.txt`: Shows you the contents of a file (like opening a file in Notepad'for Windows')

- `echo Hello || echo Hello`: Prints text to the screen (like typing in Notepad'for Windows')

- `findstr Hello || find Hello`: Searches for text in a file (like using the search bar in Notepad'for Windows')

- `cd -`: Takes you back to the last directory you were in (like going back in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `cd / || cd \`: Takes you to the root directory (like going to the top level of your files in File Explorer'for Windows')

- `cd <path>`: Takes you to a specific directory (like clicking on a folder in File Explorer'for Windows')
